commit.message:
Use C types in exported interface

The exported interface now uses CUInt and CLong instead of Integer. Although
Integer made a more idiomatic Haskell interface, it did not faithfully represent
the ALSA API.

Fixes: #6

commit.message:
Upgrade Nixpkgs infrastructure

The Nix expressions and Nixpkgs infrastructure are upgraded to a more-modern
setup used in my other projects. The project is pinned to a particular Nixpkgs
version from NixOS/nixpkgs-channels so that a binary cache is available.

commit.message:
Merge pull request #5 from nlewo/master

Use capture channel to get capture volume
Use capture channel to get capture volume

Relax unix dependency

The 'unix == 2.6.*' dependency was overly restrictive. We import only
one symbol (System.Posix.Process.getProcessID) from unix, so there is no
chance of a name collision later. The only potential problem is if
'getProcessID' were removed, a highly unlikely scenario.
Document the type of thrown exceptions
